<div id="review_2220103441" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2220103441" />
    <a title="J.M. Hushour" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17463213-j-m-hushour"><img alt="J.M. Hushour" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442964894p2/17463213.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2220103441?book_show_action=true">Dec 20, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="J.M. Hushour" class="user" itemprop="url" name="J.M. Hushour" href="/user/show/17463213-j-m-hushour">J.M. Hushour</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 014044.108" href="/book/show/36298632-the-cloud-of-unknowing">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2220103441" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9788585024222437690">&quot;Cloud&quot; is a mildly interesting 14th century text, probably written by a West Midlands country priest and reads like an instruction manual to a novice. I can break it down like this: it is a discussion of the impossibility of knowing God via the intellect, but rather through love. It is a devotional, in the full sense of the word, text, bizarrely similar to Sufi mystical rituals where the power of the name of God invoked and repeated incessantly put one into a kind of meditative trance.<br/>It&apos;s brie</span>
  <span id="freeText9788585024222437690" style="display:none">"Cloud" is a mildly interesting 14th century text, probably written by a West Midlands country priest and reads like an instruction manual to a novice. I can break it down like this: it is a discussion of the impossibility of knowing God via the intellect, but rather through love. It is a devotional, in the full sense of the word, text, bizarrely similar to Sufi mystical rituals where the power of the name of God invoked and repeated incessantly put one into a kind of meditative trance.<br />It's brief and beautifully composed, but probably not much more of a passing interest to most folks.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9788585024222437690" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


