<div id="review_2335117477" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2335117477" />
    <a title="Luke Gorham" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11654130-luke-gorham"><img alt="Luke Gorham" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1500483642p2/11654130.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2335117477?book_show_action=true">Mar 21, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Luke Gorham" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Luke Gorham" href="/user/show/11654130-luke-gorham">Luke Gorham</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11654130-luke-gorham?shelf=spirituality">spirituality</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11654130-luke-gorham?shelf=philosophy">philosophy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2335117477" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer91994577581145018">Interesting as a historical document and the immersion into mystical traditional. As theology, it is at best a conflation of cherry-picked esoterica espousing an incredibly narrow path to enlightment; at worst, it&apos;s an astoudingly egoistic manifesto written for (literally) a chosen few devotees. In fact, it&apos;s alarming how much this work&apos;s foreword has in common with modern evangelical defense systems: both basically state, if you disagree with me, it&apos;s because you are spiritually unprepared for </span>
  <span id="freeText91994577581145018" style="display:none">Interesting as a historical document and the immersion into mystical traditional. As theology, it is at best a conflation of cherry-picked esoterica espousing an incredibly narrow path to enlightment; at worst, it's an astoudingly egoistic manifesto written for (literally) a chosen few devotees. In fact, it's alarming how much this work's foreword has in common with modern evangelical defense systems: both basically state, if you disagree with me, it's because you are spiritually unprepared for the truth, you heathen. And then it continues from this, with the reliably self-involved, hyper-judgmental ravings of a withdrawn psyche. Again, there is historical/contextual merit here and a strong presention of ideas, but the pure solipsism of the ideas and my own personal, hardwon bias against this brand of theology buries this for me.</span>
  <a data-text-id="91994577581145018" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


