<div id="review_2133023630" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2133023630" />
    <a title="Poetreehugger" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2161815-poetreehugger"><img alt="Poetreehugger" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1238018032p2/2161815.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2133023630?book_show_action=true">Nov 19, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Poetreehugger" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Poetreehugger" href="/user/show/2161815-poetreehugger">Poetreehugger</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/34818978-the-cloud-of-unknowing">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2133023630" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9549410863239355536">Much archaic language in the kindle edition, by Evelyn Underhill. But edifying. Archaic wording has a unique feel to it, if one takes the time.<br/>I may reread this book in the fragile old paperback copy I have, by Ira Progoff, which seems to have more readily understood language.<br/>There is some of the sad philosophy of human intrinsic evil in here, which I do not subscribe to, but that’s not surprising in the fourteenth century.<br/>There is also much spiritual truth to contemplate.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


